#1 Metastatic rectal carcinoma to lymph node
Mrs. Camara returns following her surgery.  She underwent a surgical resection last month following her five-day course of radiation therapy.  She was found to have a T4, N2 tumor with 16 positive regional nodes.  This included tumor deposits in the pericolonic fat.  She has slowly recovered from surgery and is now returning for reevaluation.
#2 Pulmonary nodule
This was noted preoperatively.  She denies any new respiratory symptoms.

